    <h1>The Rim</h1>
    <p class="lede">The Rim is the edge-place of Vaelinya: a borderland between nearer and farther ways of living, travelling, and belonging.</p>
    <p>It is a strong first place to enter the world because it shows one of Vaelinya’s core ideas: borders are places as well as lines. People meet there, cross there, carry stories there, make agreements there, and learn to notice what changes.</p>
    <p>Life on the Rim is shaped by weather, route, shelter, trade, listening, and careful attention to other people. A road may be practical, sacred, dangerous, familiar, or all of those things at once.</p>
    <p>The people of the Rim are known among themselves as the Rimaeri. Their lives are shaped by movement, fairness, remembrance, and the work of keeping connection across difference.</p>
    <p>For a new reader, the Rim helps Vaelinya feel like a living world rather than a flat map. It asks: what does a border do to a person, a family, a song, a promise, or a child trying to understand where they belong?</p>
